description:
John went from being a ‘Son of Thunder’ to ‘John the Beloved’, a remarkable change in character and he would go on to write five books of the New Testament. John was the only disciple to die a natural death and spent time on the beautiful and barren isle of Patmos in his later years where he wrote the book of Revelation after receiving a vision from God. This book has intrigued, inspired and guided Gods people since then, till now and will continue to do so until Jesus comes.
